 Dr. Abdullahi Kabir of the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Teaching Hospital, Bauchi, has advised mothers planning for new babies to seek pre-conception care, for optimal outcome during delivery. Kabir gave the advice in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Friday in Bauchi. According to him, the care is seeking to guide mothers on the right time to have babies and reduce the burden of having complications during ante-natal clinics and delivery. Continue reading Gynaecologist advises mothers on pre- conception care for optimal delivery at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard